  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Myanmar Floods 2015</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Since mid-July heavy monsoon rains have caused floods and triggered landslides in several parts of Myanmar. The situation worsened on 30 July when Cyclone Komen brought with it high winds and further heavy rain. More than 100 people have died and over 1.5 million people have been affected. Almost 300 000 households have been displaced and over 15 000 homes have been destroyed. The flooding is spread over a large area (see red areas on map) largely in the northwest west south and southwest of the country; affecting 12 of Myanmar s 15 states. This disaster is still evolving. While floodwaters are subsiding in some places many areas including towns and rural areas remain inundated and further rainfall and flooding is predicted. The government has urged people to evacuate in areas further south in the country where rivers are running at danger levels and further flooding is expected.</narrative>
  </description>
